Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The experts group of India and China today began 
their three-day talks on reduction of troop level along the line 
of actual control. The 12-member Chinese delegation consisting 
of top army personnel and diplomats is led by the deputy 
director in the foreign ministry, Mr. Fu Xuezhang. The Indian 
delegation is led by the joint secretary in the External Affairs 
Ministry, Mr. Shiv Kumar Menon. 

